Univariate Analysis

Explore Data set attribute to get insight

Most wine quiality falls under 5-6 score. Kind of normal distribution since it’s (low-high-low) The distribution has no outliers.

The plot of fixed acidity is positively skewed, about 60 wine has around 8-10 Aacidity and there is outliers. Thats why the mean (8.32) is larger than median (7.9)

The mean of Volatile Acidity is 0.52 & median is also 0.52 but it’s not normal distribution it’s bimodal as the bar plot shows. There is outliers.

Critic Acid has a mean of 0.27 and median of 0.26 the distribution is low with two individual peaks and one outlier of high critic acidity This might indicate a poor data gathering or governance of the sensors.

Residual Sugar has a mean of 2.54 and median of 2.2. Which justify the positively skewed graph at 2; outliers of high resifual sugar exists.

Chlorides has a mean of 0.9 and median of 0.8 It’s also positively skewed at 0.1 Chlorides has outliers.

Free Sulfur Dioxide has a mean of 15.87 and median of 14 Right skewed and most wines tops free sulfur dioxide at 140 , outliers exists

Total Sulfur Dioxide has a mean of 46 and median of 38. As this attribute and the previous one present the same chemical propery they share thame distribution

Density has a mean of 0.99 and median of 0.99 from mean & median and the plot we are firm it’s normal distribution

pH has a mean of 3.31 and median of 3.31 from mean & median and the plot we are firm it’s normal distribution

Sulphates has a mean of 0.65 and median of 0.62 positively skewed between 0.5-0.75 and has outliers.

Alcohol has a mean of 10.42 and median of 10.20 Right skewed and most wines tops free sulfur dioxide at 7 , outliers exists

For the quality relationships with other features:

  • Alcohol and Sulaphate amount affects wine positively.
  • Citric Acid, has minor affect of improving the wine quality.

Were there any interesting or surprising interactions between features?

The three acidity features, Volatile acidity, critic acidity and fixed acidity. Fixed acidity and volatile acidity has negative correlation. but Fixed acidity and critic acid has positive correlation.

OPTIONAL: Did you create any models with your dataset?

The model is built with 6 attributes of strong or negative correlation. The model summary: quality = 2.985 + 0.276xalcohol - 2.985xvolatile.acidity + 0.908xsulphates + 0.065xcitric.acid - -1.763*chlorides - 0.002xtotal.sulfur.dioxide There was not enough information decide confidence level. Value of R squared value are low, alcohol contributes to 22% of the Wine Quality. The lack of many information may be due of containing ‘Average’ quality wines in the dataset.

Reflection

The major contribution to quality of the features is alcohol, which is predictable and the analysis is right. Also, Sulfates has a small positive contribution. Its normally used to prevent rotting. A down side contribution to quality is Volatile acidity , Volatile acidity affects to the acidic taste. I struggled with lack of data to statistics. also with data accuracy and data collection. Some were not reasonable. Most correlation went as expected and the overall analysis is expected.

Positive Correlation: 1. Density with Fixed Acidity. Which is reasonable 2. Quality and Alcohol. which is also reasonable 3. Fixed acidity and critic acid.

Negative: 1. The strongest correlation in the plot is between Volatile acidity and pH. Though, they should be negative since pH is a base that sould lower the acidity. 2. Alcohol with density. Mathmatically as water increases alcohol dissolves. 3. Fixed acidity and volatile acidity What surprised how pH and volatile acidity are positively correlated. The data could use a better data collection and raw data without average modificaton. A linear model is build upon 6 features.

I personally didn’t like R, it’s exhausting. As a data analyst I usually use python, matlab at worse. It’s good that I have a basic knowledge about the great language but I don’t prefer it as my top skill.

For Future work, get a better data obviously and more features that describe the wine such where it was made, how long has it been stored and other ingredients not mentioned in the dataset.
